    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1904-05-02T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1904-05-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="890"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d890">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Leishman</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Constantinople</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-05-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 2, 1904</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 778.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: * * * I inclose copy of note just received from
                    the Sublime Porte officially confirming the promise that proper steps would be
                    taken to arrest the murderer of Missionary Labaree in case he attempt to enter
                    Turkish territory.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John G. A. Leishman.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#center">[Inclosure.—Translation.]</seg>
                    </opener>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">
                            <persName type="from">Tewfik Pasha</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to"
                                >Leishman</persName>.</hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Sublime Porte, Ministry of Foreign Affairs</hi>,<lb/>
                                <hi rend="italic">Constantinople</hi>
                            </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-04-30">
                                <hi rend="italic">April 30, 1904</hi>
                            </date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Me. Envoy</hi>: In answer to the note that your
                        excellency addressed to me, dated the 26th of March last, No. 382, I have
                        the honor to inform you, according to a telegram of the governor-general of
                        the vilayet of Erzeroum, that categoric <pb facs="0924" n="836"
                            xml:id="pg_836"/> orders have been given to the civil and military
                        authorities for the arrest of Seyid Ghaffar, accused of having assassinated
                        the American missionary Labaree in Persia, in the event of his passing into
                        Ottoman territory.</p>
                    <p>Accept, sir, etc.,</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tewfik.</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
